    <main class="page-shell">
      <section class="article-intro" aria-labelledby="article-title">
        <div class="article-intro__inner">
          <p class="article-kicker">Project Draft</p>
          <h1 class="article-title" id="article-title">Artemis II and the New Contractor State</h1>
          <p class="article-subtitle">A working article about what the Artemis program reveals about NASA’s dependence on private industry, and how that relationship has changed since Apollo.</p>
          <p class="article-copy">Artemis II, which safely returned last weekend, marked a historic return to manned lunar spaceflight, but it is also a historic launch because of the scale of industrial coordination required to make it possible.</p>
          <p class="article-copy">The broader Artemis program carries an unprecedented budget measured in the tens of billions of dollars, and a large share of that cost comes from the fact that so many parts of the launch stack had to be custom designed, manufactured, integrated, and certified for this mission architecture in order for the SLS to be “the only rocket that can send Orion, astronauts, and supplies to the Moon in a single mission.”</p>

          <section class="inline-diagram diagram-panel is-price-mode" data-diagram-panel data-initial-mode="prices" data-inline-simple="true" aria-label="Diagram 1: Artemis II price diagram">
            <aside class="panel" aria-label="Artemis II price key">
              <section class="price-legend" aria-labelledby="inline-price-title">
